text: Paid $4.30 for a plate of roasted duck rice. The duck meat was moist, tender and tasty. The soup was tasty too. Service was friendly and efficient. Very limited seats in the eatery during peak hours. Previously, I had tried the prawn dumpling noodle and this was not recommended.
The roasted pork is quite good and the portion is generous considering the price. Will visit again.

The economic rice stall can skipped. Rice is abit under cooked.
I am dinning in not packet out. (At around 1315pm) The vegetables and meat slices i ordered are cold.
Curry sauce very salty.
Basically, only the curry sauce is warm.
Seriously, not worth.
Who will want to pay to eat cold food? And this is not the 1st time already.
$7, 2veg 1meat chai fan not worth , price kept changing. Never coming back
Small Coffee Shop but great variety of local food. Good value for money.
